'''Kim Moon-hwan''' ({{langx|ko|김문환}}; born 1 August 1995) is a South Korean professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full back|right-back]] for [[K League 1]] club [[Daejeon Hana Citizen]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].<ref name="sw">{{Soccerway |id=moon-hwan-kim/476705 |archive=20240615064930}}</ref>

==Club career==
After attending [[Chung-Ang University]] for three years,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=9523963&memberNo=1744834&searchKeyword=%EA%B9%80%EB%AC%B8%ED%99%98&searchRank=5 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210414231040/https://post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=9523963&memberNo=1744834&searchKeyword=%EA%B9%80%EB%AC%B8%ED%99%98&searchRank=5 |script-title=ko:부산의 특급 신인, '그 분' 닮은 김문환의 꿈 |website=Naver |last=Seo |first=Hyung-wook |date=2017-09-11 |access-date=2026-04-14 |archive-date=2021-04-14}}</ref> Kim signed for [[K League 2]] club [[Busan IPark]] on 3 January 2017.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=6023873&memberNo=4179311&vType=VERTICAL |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622005243/https://m.post.naver.com/viewer/postView.nhn?volumeNo=6023873&memberNo=4179311&vType=VERTICAL |script-title=ko:부산의 미래를 책임질 신인 김정호, 김문환 영입 |website=Naver |publisher=Busan IPark |date=2017-01-03 |access-date=2026-04-14 |archive-date=2018-06-22}}</ref> He played as a forward until his university days, whereas starting to play as a right-back at Busan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nocutnews.co.kr/news/5851813 |script-title=ko:"故 조진호 감독님이 떠올랐어요" WC 만든 김문환의 포지션 변경 |language=ko |publisher=No Cut News |date=2022-11-18 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref> In his first professional season, the club reached the finals at both the promotion play-offs and the [[Korean FA Cup]], but lost the two finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20171203043900007 |script-title=ko:승격 실패에 FA컵 준우승까지…또다시 '눈물' 흘린 부산 |language=ko |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2017-12-03 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

In 2018 and 2019, Kim was evaluated as the best right-back of the K League 2, being named in the [[K League Best XI#K League 2 award|league's Best XI]]. He became a [[K League 1]] player in 2020 after helping Busan win the promotion play-offs.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sports-g.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=87631 |script-title=ko:부산 김문환 "故조진호 감독 향한 기도, 드디어 이루어졌다" |language=ko |publisher=Sports-G |date=2019-12-08 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

After Busan finished bottom of the K League 1, Kim joined [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Los Angeles FC]] on 11 January 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.lafc.com/post/2021/01/11/lafc-signs-korean-international-kim-moon-hwan |title=LAFC Signs Korean International Kim Moon-Hwan |publisher=Los Angeles FC |date=2021-01-12 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref> He played four matches as a substitute during LAFC's first eight matches due to an aftereffect of knee injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/players/kim-moon-hwan/match-log/ |title=Kim Moon-Hwan, Match Log |publisher=Major League Soccer |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref> On 24 June, he made his first MLS start in a 2–0 win over [[FC Dallas]], where he was named the Man of the Match.<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=Los Angeles FC |user=LAFC |number=1408094245185937414 |title=Your @LAFC3252 Man of the Match, Kim Moon-Hwan!}}</ref> He made 28 appearances including 20 starts for about a year at LAFC.<ref name="sw"/>

On 18 March 2022, Kim transferred to K League 1 side [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]].<ref>{{cite web |date=18 March 2022 |title=LAFC Transfers Kim Moon-Hwan To K-League Club Jeonbuk Hyundai |url=https://www.lafc.com/news/lafc-transfers-kim-moon-hwan-to-k-league-club-jeonbuk-hyundai |access-date=18 March 2022 |publisher=Los Angeles FC}}</ref> He judged that playing for Jeonbuk was more likely to be selected for the South Korean squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20220319023900007 |script-title=ko:K리그1 전북, 국가대표급 풀백 김문환 영입 임박…"메디컬 남아" |language=ko |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2022-03-19 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref> After winning the [[2022 Korean FA Cup]] with Jeonbuk, he was called up to the national team for the World Cup.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.hankooki.com/news/articleView.html?idxno=6812726 |script-title=ko:송종국 잇는 '우측면의 신형 엔진' 김문환, ‘첫 월드컵’서 선발 꿰찰까[월드컵 태극전사 소개 15] |language=ko |publisher=Sports Hankook |date=2022-11-18 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

==International career==
Kim played for the [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea under-23 team]] at both the [[2018 AFC U-23 Championship]] and the [[Football at the 2018 Asian Games – Men's tournament|2018 Asian Games]].<ref name="kfa"/> Kim and his teammates won a gold at the latter, earning their exemption from military service.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sportsq.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=457461 |script-title=ko:아시안게임 군면제 20명, 한국 축구 날개 달았다 |language=ko |publisher=Sports Q |date=2023-10-08 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

On 7 September 2018, Kim made his senior international debut as a substitute in a 2–0 win over [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].<ref name="kfa"/> On 16 January 2019, he played as a starter for the national team for the first time in an [[AFC Asian Cup]] match against [[China national football team|China]], which ended in a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kookje.co.kr/news2011/asp/newsbody.asp?code=0600&key=20190116.22022006005 |script-title=ko:이용 그늘에 가린 김문환…중국전 빛 볼까 |language=ko |publisher=The Kookje Daily News |date=2019-01-15 |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], Kim played all 360 minutes for South Korea until the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fbref.com/en/players/6bce7dd8/matchlogs/2022/Kim-Moonhwan-Match-Logs |title=Kim Moonhwan 2022 Match Logs |publisher=FBref |access-date=2026-04-14}}</ref>

